{
  "doc_id": "58289",
  "text": "Problem (1), introduced and studied by Moré [CITATION_1] , Stern and Wolkowicz [CITATION_2] , generalizes the classical Trust-Region Subproblem (TRS) [6] in which one is asked to optimize a nonconvex quadratic objective over a Euclidean ball. The TRS is an essential ingredient of trust-region methods that are commonly used to solve continuous nonconvex optimization problems [6, [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] and also arises in applications such as robust optimization [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] . On the other hand, the GTRS has applications in nonconvex quadratic integer programs, signal processing, and compressed sensing; see [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] and references therein for more applications.",
